    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Spring 5.3.x Open Source Support ended on August 31th 2024 (<a href=\"https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/wiki/Spring-Framework-Versions#supported-versions\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">source</a>). This means that v5.3.40 is only available for commercial support, and can't be found on a central Maven repository (<a href=\"https://spring.io/security/cve-2024-38816\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">source</a>).</p>\n<p>If you don't have commercial support, you're supposed to update to Spring 6.1.13 (Spring Boot 3.x), which does exist on central Maven repositories.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Maven (pom.xml)</li>\n</ul>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n    &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework&lt;/groupId&gt;\n    &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-webmvc&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n    &lt;version&gt;6.1.13&lt;/version&gt; &lt;!-- This works --&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Gradle (build.gradle)</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><code>implementation 'org.springframework:spring-webmvc:6.1.13' //This works\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
